n&lt;button id=\"my_element\">Click me&lt;/button>\n\n// JavaScript\ndocument.getElementById(\"my_element\").addEventListener(\"click\", ...);</code></pre></div>\n<p>In this case, <code class=\"language-text\">my_element</code> is going to be the <code class=\"language-text\">event.currentTarget</code>.</p>\n<p>On the other hand, <code class=\"language-text\">event.target</code> is any element (or any of its children) that triggered the event, for example:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">// HTML\n&lt;p> This &lt;b>is&lt;/b> a &lt;span>paragraph&lt;/span>.&lt;/p>\n\n// JavaScript\ndocument.querySelector(\"p\").addEventListener(\"click\", ...);</code></pre></div>\n<p>In this case, clicking on any element will trigger the\nevent listener, but <code class=\"language-text\">event.target</code> will be the specific element that was clicked,\nin this case, <code class=\"language-text\">p</code>, <code class=\"language-text\">b</code> or <code class=\"language-text\">span</code>.</p>\n<p>The code below makes this explanation a bit more clear:</p>\n<iframe height=\"334.5621337890625\" style=\"width: 100%;\" scrolling=\"no\" title=\"target vs currentTarget\" src=\"https://codepen.io/jpedroribeiro/embed/zYLLdJV?default-tab=result\" frameborder=\"no\" loading=\"lazy\" allowtransparency=\"true\" allowfullscreen=\"true\">\n  See the Pen <a href=\"https://codepen.io/jpedroribeiro/pen/zYLLdJV\">\n  target vs currentTarget</a> by Pedro Ribeiro (<a href=\"https://codepen.io/jpedroribeiro\">@jpedroribeiro</a>)\n  on <a href=\"https://codepen.io\">CodePen</a>.\n</iframe>","frontmatter":{"title":"event.target vs event.currentTarget - What is the difference?","date":"January 29, 2023"}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/2023/01/event-target-vs-event-currenttarget/","previous":{"fields":{"slug":"/2022/12/dangerouslySetInnerHTML-did-not-match/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"How to fix 'dangerouslySetInnerHTML did not match' error in React.js","tags":["reactjs","javascript","nextjs","ssr"]}},"next":{"fields":{"slug":"/2023/03/sliding-puzzle-game-in-javascript/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Sliding Puzzle Game in JavaScript","tags":["game","javascript","puzzle","node"]}}}},"staticQueryHashes":["63159454","792910177"],"slicesMap":{}}